1
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,070
However,

2
00:00:13,510 --> 00:00:15,200
when I was about to induce vomiting,

3
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:17,950
Zhang Cong changed his mind.

4
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:28,310
Don't make a sound.

5
00:00:28,560 --> 00:00:29,880
Stay put.

6
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:31,879
He'll die.

7
00:00:31,880 --> 00:00:32,919
=Cases Between Us=

8
00:00:32,920 --> 00:00:34,269
He has to die

9
00:00:34,270 --> 00:00:36,019
for me to survive.

10
00:00:36,020 --> 00:00:37,759
=Episode 26=

11
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:38,950
Dr. Ge,

12
00:00:39,270 --> 00:00:41,240
unless you want to end up dead.

13
00:00:42,990 --> 00:00:44,670
He's your senior.

14
00:00:44,990 --> 00:00:46,390
Why try to kill him?

15
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:48,350
It isn't me who wants him dead,

16
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,910
it's Master Hu.

17
00:01:01,310 --> 00:01:02,590
Zhang,

18
00:01:03,350 --> 00:01:04,750
I'm sorry.

19
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:08,310
Master Hu offered me too much.

20
00:01:08,630 --> 00:01:10,750
Rest easy.

21
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,080
I will

22
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:14,310
take good care

23
00:01:15,150 --> 00:01:16,520
of the Zhang troupe.

24
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:15,710
Zhang Dalu wasn't dead?

25
00:02:17,110 --> 00:02:18,999
Years of training made him

26
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,920
much tougher than most people.

27
00:02:21,070 --> 00:02:22,520
I never imagined

28
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:24,950
he'd wake up on his own.

29
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,320
Uh,

30
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,039
what happened then?

31
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,600
I induced vomiting,

32
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,480
and he left.

33
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,270
Where did he go?

34
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:35,640
No idea.

35
00:02:39,830 --> 00:02:40,760
By the way,

36
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,200
not long after,

37
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:45,240
Zhang Cong came back.

38
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:47,080
What do you want?

39
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,879
Where's Zhang Dalu?

40
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:52,019
Is he still alive?

41
00:02:52,020 --> 00:02:53,990
Is he still alive?

42
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,159
He's definitely dead.

43
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:56,879
No.

44
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:57,599
He's not.

45
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:59,549
His hands were warm.

46
00:02:59,550 --> 00:03:01,349
I doubled the dose.

47
00:03:01,350 --> 00:03:02,509
How could he still be alive?

48
00:03:02,510 --> 00:03:04,150
He's alive.

49
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,069
What did you say? You doubled the dose?

50
00:03:06,070 --> 00:03:07,479
You said

51
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,629
it'd kill him if the dose doubled.

52
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:11,059
He must've gone there.

53
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:12,760
He must've gone there.

54
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:16,920
Where is "there" Zhang Cong mentioned?

55
00:03:18,770 --> 00:03:20,600
I had no idea

56
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:23,040
what happened after that.

57
00:03:24,110 --> 00:03:25,990
Did you bring Ge Fan in?

58
00:03:36,390 --> 00:03:37,990
What are you doing here?

59
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:50,980
(661 Beijing)

60
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,070
Watch the road.

61
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:26,550
Why did you go to the station?

62
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,919
I happened to pass your clinic.

63
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:31,349
I was going to see you,

64
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:33,040
but they said the police took you away.

65
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:34,750
Why did you come looking for me?

66
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:36,190
Nothing.

67
00:04:43,230 --> 00:04:43,989
Well,

68
00:04:43,990 --> 00:04:46,190
I just wanted to ask you

69
00:04:46,790 --> 00:04:48,310
about something medical.

70
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:51,240
Medical?

71
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,989
Where are you headed?

72
00:05:01,990 --> 00:05:03,240
Back to the clinic.

73
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:04,549
It's late.

74
00:05:04,550 --> 00:05:05,600
Are you not going home?

75
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:09,840
I live at the clinic.

76
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:11,960
I see.

77
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:45,840
You came at the right time.

78
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:47,550
Zhang Cong confessed.

79
00:05:47,670 --> 00:05:49,039
Hu Mingwu paid him off

80
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,630
to kill Zhang Dalu.

81
00:05:50,990 --> 00:05:52,109
After leaving the clinic,

82
00:05:52,110 --> 00:05:53,839
he went to the house at Shanjiankou.

83
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,920
He planned to finish Zhang Dalu off,

84
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,750
only to find him dead from the poison.

85
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,399
No wonder Douding couldn't find him

86
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,519
after leaving the cheap inn.

87
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,599
He was moving the body.

88
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,749
That's right.
He had to prove it to Hu Mingwu.

89
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:04,749
What is this?

90
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:06,280
I brought you some zenggao
[*Made with glutinous rice flour and dates]

91
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:09,009
and treats for him.

92
00:06:09,010 --> 00:06:09,920
Here.

93
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,800
Everything seems to fall into place.

94
00:06:14,190 --> 00:06:15,400
Yes,

95
00:06:15,670 --> 00:06:17,510
but something feels off.

96
00:06:18,190 --> 00:06:19,190
Xiaoyuan.

97
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,360
What feels off?

98
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,189
Who are you calling?

99
00:06:28,190 --> 00:06:29,360
The dog.

100
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,960
Shouldn't your dog have your surname?

101
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,349
Don't make up names.

102
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:35,630
It already has one.

103
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,159
Really?

104
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,160
What's its name?

105
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,429
Young Master.

106
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:39,430
Young Master...

107
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:40,719
Let's go, Young Master.

108
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,960
What, Young Master?

109
00:06:42,550 --> 00:06:44,959
Who are you trying to insult?
Who are you calling "Young Master"?

110
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:45,789
Did I say you could?

111
00:06:45,790 --> 00:06:46,739
"Young Master", huh?

112
00:06:46,739 --> 00:06:48,410
You think anyone can be called
"Young Master"?

113
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,869
Did I give you permission
to name the dog that?

114
00:06:50,870 --> 00:06:52,070
Young Master, huh?

115
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:06,869
The clinic is quiet at noon.

116
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:07,920
Nice.

117
00:07:12,190 --> 00:07:13,990
Dr. Cheng isn't back yet?

118
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:19,399
Aren't you picking him up
at the station later?

119
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:20,480
Right.

120
00:07:25,990 --> 00:07:27,310
I'll do it.

121
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:48,240
Why did Dr. Cheng

122
00:07:48,350 --> 00:07:49,630
leave Peking Union?

123
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:52,600
I'm not sure.

124
00:07:52,870 --> 00:07:53,669
But I know

125
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:55,240
he resigned willingly.

126
00:07:56,230 --> 00:07:57,920
That was Peking Union.

127
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,630
Top facilities and equipment.

128
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:03,630
If I could work there,

129
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:05,349
I'd become

130
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:06,600
an even better doctor.

131
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,989
I think you can do

132
00:08:08,990 --> 00:08:10,550
just as well here.

133
00:08:11,670 --> 00:08:13,280
Dr. Cheng always believed

134
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:15,600
medical care in South City
wasn't good enough.

135
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:18,919
He thought

136
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:19,989
ordinary people

137
00:08:19,990 --> 00:08:21,430
couldn't afford big hospitals,

138
00:08:21,990 --> 00:08:24,039
and quacks weren't skilled enough.

139
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,670
So he'd always wanted
to open a free clinic.

140
00:08:25,790 --> 00:08:26,789
I believe

141
00:08:26,790 --> 00:08:28,070
that's what makes the best doctor.

142
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:31,960
You mean he came back because...

143
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:33,339
The moment you walk into this clinic,

144
00:08:33,339 --> 00:08:34,390
the wall

145
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:37,030
full of thank-you banners

146
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,480
says it all.

147
00:08:41,710 --> 00:08:42,790
Dr. Ge,

148
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,159
are you wondering

149
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:47,469
if Dr. Cheng still has influence

150
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:48,790
at Peking Union?

151
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,189
I did train

152
00:08:55,190 --> 00:08:57,429
at Peking Union.

153
00:08:57,430 --> 00:08:59,270
I was fortunate enough
to study under Dr. Cheng.

154
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,910
He said

155
00:09:02,070 --> 00:09:03,789
that after our five-year apprenticeship,

156
00:09:03,790 --> 00:09:04,919
he'd recommend

157
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,390
the best student among us

158
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,790
to become a doctor at Peking Union.

159
00:09:10,070 --> 00:09:11,429
You're second-in-command

160
00:09:11,430 --> 00:09:12,789
in this clinic now.

161
00:09:12,790 --> 00:09:14,870
That shows how highly
Dr. Cheng thinks of you.

162
00:09:15,590 --> 00:09:16,960
I won't claim that.

163
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:17,949
But

164
00:09:17,950 --> 00:09:20,320
I'm definitely the hardest-working
in the class.

165
00:09:20,470 --> 00:09:22,359
So Dr. Cheng's recommendation

166
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:24,390
is a ticket to Peking Union.

167
00:09:28,590 --> 00:09:30,949
Do you think you could

168
00:09:30,950 --> 00:09:32,709
sound him out for me?

169
00:09:32,710 --> 00:09:33,680
No problem.

170
00:09:33,950 --> 00:09:35,429
I'll ask him for you

171
00:09:35,430 --> 00:09:36,960
when I pick him up.

172
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:38,480
Thanks.

173
00:09:45,950 --> 00:09:46,720
Chief.

174
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,800
We found something at the Zhang troupe.

175
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:51,220
We found this hidden in a compartment
under Zhang Dalu's pillow chest.

176
00:09:51,950 --> 00:09:52,669
What is this?

177
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:54,680
The lab confirmed it's tetrodotoxin.

178
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:07,910
Dr. Cheng,

179
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,639
your trainees are about to finish

180
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:12,240
their five-year program, aren't they?

181
00:10:12,470 --> 00:10:14,680
I heard you're recommending
one of them to Peking Union.

182
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,110
Have you decided who?

183
00:10:22,590 --> 00:10:25,030
If not,

184
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,480
what do you think of Ge Fan?

185
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,919
Ge is the student

186
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,990
I'm proudest of.

187
00:10:33,310 --> 00:10:34,720
But I won't be giving her

188
00:10:34,790 --> 00:10:36,150
that recommendation.

189
00:10:37,190 --> 00:10:38,240
Why not?

190
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:41,080
Come in.

191
00:10:54,950 --> 00:10:56,750
There's one thing I'm curious about.

192
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:00,320
Ge Fan and you
are from completely different worlds.

193
00:11:00,590 --> 00:11:02,320
Why did she listen to
everything you said?

194
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:07,200
Have you heard of this?
"You can never tell with people".

195
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:09,270
Do you really think

196
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:11,630
she's innocent?

197
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,560
Please wait for your turn.

198
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,270
Are you going to confess,

199
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,840
or do you want me to say it?

200
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:32,750
Say what?

201
00:11:33,310 --> 00:11:34,440
What did I do?

202
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,119
You never tried

203
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:37,480
to save Zhang Dalu.

204
00:11:38,790 --> 00:11:39,840
Because

205
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:44,480
he never took the fake-death drug.

206
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,879
One of the younger performers
in the Zhang troupe

207
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,390
is from Yangzhou.

208
00:11:51,430 --> 00:11:54,159
The night before the performance,
Zhang Dalu was extremely nervous.

209
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:56,080
He grabbed the boy and asked,

210
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:58,240
"How many cases of pufferfish poisoning

211
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,150
have you seen?"

212
00:12:04,590 --> 00:12:06,549
Most of them died.

213
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:07,639
One was paralyzed,

214
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,270
and another suffered
permanent brain damage.

215
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:12,840
Do you think

216
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,510
he still dared to take the drug

217
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:15,910
after hearing that?

218
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:19,789
Dalu!

219
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:20,549
Stay outside.

220
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:21,630
Don't come in.

221
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,159
Please wait outside.

222
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:24,879
Don't worry.

223
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,910
Dr. Ge will do everything she can
to save him.

224
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:32,399
Don't sit up.

225
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:33,519
People will notice.

226
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,720
Dr. Ge,

227
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,750
I didn't take the pill.

228
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:38,150
What did you say?

229
00:12:39,830 --> 00:12:40,840
It's fine.

230
00:12:41,190 --> 00:12:43,200
You won't fool them like this.

231
00:12:43,550 --> 00:12:44,879
I'll give it a try.

232
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:46,320
If it doesn't work,

233
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:48,080
I'll accept whatever happens to me.

234
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,270
Do you have an ice pack?

235
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:05,870
You've got quite the imagination.

236
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:06,840
Do you solve cases

237
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:08,320
by guessing?

238
00:13:12,670 --> 00:13:14,960
The tetrodotoxin pill
Zhang Dalu didn't take

239
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,910
was found in this room.

240
00:13:17,190 --> 00:13:19,320
How did you know it was tetrodotoxin?

241
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:20,840
Why don't you try it yourself?

242
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,390
Not only did you fool the one-eyed man,

243
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:29,709
but also Zhang Cong.

244
00:13:29,710 --> 00:13:31,270
He never knew Zhang Dalu hadn't taken it.

245
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:33,030
That's why

246
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,910
he kept stopping you

247
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,600
to help Zhang Dalu induce vomiting.

248
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:38,790
He wanted to kill you.

249
00:13:38,830 --> 00:13:40,510
Why did you let him go?

250
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:45,480
We've been friends for over ten years.

251
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:50,270
Forget it.

252
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:56,440
I survived, didn't I?

253
00:13:57,590 --> 00:13:58,870
Thank you.

254
00:14:05,190 --> 00:14:06,240
Wait here.

255
00:14:08,590 --> 00:14:10,270
I'll get your clothes.

256
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:32,309
Everything you've said

257
00:14:32,310 --> 00:14:33,840
is just speculation.

258
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:35,840
Where's your evidence?

259
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:38,519
Dry the pufferfish liver,
grind it into powder,

260
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:40,240
then purify it in a pomegranate jar.

261
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,840
The toxin becomes highly concentrated.

262
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,440
It works much faster
than Zhang Cong's method.

263
00:14:45,790 --> 00:14:47,189
It has almost no incubation period.

264
00:14:47,190 --> 00:14:49,240
It takes effect
within ten minutes or so.

265
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:55,789
The moment Zhang Dalu felt unwell,

266
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:57,069
he'd eat Strength Pills.

267
00:14:57,070 --> 00:14:58,270
That was his habit.

268
00:14:58,830 --> 00:14:59,549
Judging by

269
00:14:59,550 --> 00:15:01,870
the digestion of the sixteen pills
found in his stomach,

270
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:05,469
less than an hour passed
between the poisoning and his death.

271
00:15:05,470 --> 00:15:08,159
Working backward
a thirty-minute incubation period,

272
00:15:08,160 --> 00:15:10,200
he would've taken the poison

273
00:15:10,590 --> 00:15:12,030
at around 8:30 PM.

274
00:15:13,430 --> 00:15:14,560
8:30 PM?

275
00:15:14,710 --> 00:15:15,829
I was at the clinic.

276
00:15:15,830 --> 00:15:17,680
You didn't need to be there.

277
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,630
As the star performer
of the Zhang troupe,

278
00:15:21,710 --> 00:15:25,469
Zhang Dalu ate every two or three hours
to maintain his physique

279
00:15:25,470 --> 00:15:26,960
and keep his protein intake up.

280
00:15:28,790 --> 00:15:29,709
At 8:30 PM,

281
00:15:29,710 --> 00:15:31,279
he happened to eat

282
00:15:31,280 --> 00:15:33,119
the beef jerky you poisoned.

283
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,639
I also found his clothes

284
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,189
at the Zhang troupe.

285
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:39,270
They had your fingerprints on them.

286
00:15:44,550 --> 00:15:45,519
She

287
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:47,039
is a woman.

288
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:49,110
Women get married eventually.

289
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:50,669
Once she does,

290
00:15:50,670 --> 00:15:52,240
her family will come before

291
00:15:52,710 --> 00:15:54,270
the hospital.

292
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:57,270
That position

293
00:15:57,310 --> 00:15:58,990
would go to waste.

294
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,240
It's really hard for women doctors.

295
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,239
Why not give her a chance

296
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,270
to prove herself?

297
00:16:06,190 --> 00:16:07,469
There would've been

298
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:09,600
no need to dwell on this

299
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:13,240
if Tao Zhi hadn't died.

300
00:16:13,470 --> 00:16:14,630
Tao Zhi?

301
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,949
Are you talking about

302
00:16:16,950 --> 00:16:18,790
the oldest male student you took on?

303
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,560
He was the one

304
00:16:21,950 --> 00:16:24,790
I planned to recommend to Peking Union.

305
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,240
But last year,

306
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,240
he died.

307
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:33,200
He jumped in to save a drowning child

308
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,510
and never made it back out.

309
00:16:36,070 --> 00:16:38,039
Ge Fan was right there.

310
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,440
There was a bamboo pole at her feet.

311
00:16:40,470 --> 00:16:42,750
She could've saved him
without much effort.

312
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:45,080
But she did nothing.

313
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,360
She just stood there
and watched him drown.

314
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:49,589
As luck would have it,

315
00:16:49,590 --> 00:16:51,630
I saw the whole thing.

316
00:16:52,280 --> 00:16:54,030
If I didn't have that over her,

317
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,870
do you think someone so arrogant

318
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:58,960
would've obediently done
everything I told her?

319
00:17:02,550 --> 00:17:04,270
If he told Dr. Cheng,

320
00:17:05,990 --> 00:17:08,310
I'd never get into Peking Union.

321
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:11,469
You took two lives

322
00:17:11,470 --> 00:17:13,200
for one job opportunity.

323
00:17:13,710 --> 00:17:14,880
Was it worth it?

324
00:17:25,270 --> 00:17:26,640
I came from a poor family.

325
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:28,429
At sixteen,

326
00:17:28,430 --> 00:17:30,229
my family sold me for 30 silver coins

327
00:17:30,230 --> 00:17:31,880
to marry a dying man
as a good-luck bride.

328
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:34,590
Too bad I was too hard to kill.

329
00:17:34,710 --> 00:17:36,119
Instead of bringing him good luck,

330
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:38,200
I sent him to a grave.

331
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,350
The night I escaped to Beijing,

332
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:45,550
I spent the whole night
hiding in a pile of coal.

333
00:17:48,230 --> 00:17:49,550
As a woman,

334
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:52,070
there weren't many jobs I could do.

335
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:54,189
I worked while attending a girls' school.

336
00:17:54,190 --> 00:17:56,030
You have no idea
how much I've gone through

337
00:17:58,120 --> 00:17:59,480
to get where I am today.

338
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:11,070
These hands could've saved lives,

339
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:14,440
but you chose to kill with them.

340
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:21,830
Do you not regret it?

341
00:18:25,990 --> 00:18:27,750
I was clearly more capable

342
00:18:29,990 --> 00:18:32,030
than my senior, Tao Zhi.

343
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:34,880
Even Dr. Cheng said more than once

344
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:36,469
that I had greater talent.

345
00:18:36,470 --> 00:18:37,790
But in the end,

346
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:41,200
he still favored him.

347
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:44,350
Why?

348
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:47,510
Just because he was a man.

349
00:18:50,710 --> 00:18:52,160
You all say

350
00:18:53,510 --> 00:18:55,400
these are hands meant to save lives.

351
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:58,120
But to Dr. Cheng,

352
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:06,270
they're just a woman's hands.

353
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:13,020
(End of Episode 26)

354
00:19:14,441 --> 00:19:16,081
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

355
00:19:16,081 --> 00:19:17,621
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

356
00:19:17,621 --> 00:19:18,871
♪However, the world changes♪

357
00:19:18,871 --> 00:19:20,791
♪You'll still be by my side♪

358
00:19:20,791 --> 00:19:22,481
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

359
00:19:22,481 --> 00:19:24,051
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

360
00:19:24,051 --> 00:19:25,621
♪If this is my final chapter♪

361
00:19:25,621 --> 00:19:28,121
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
